item.title: There they're and their
item.dc:creator: @reyx7 reyx7
item.description:
@reyx7 wrote:

Perhaps an explaination?

There - referring to a place, follows a preposition
To go there; over there

Their - A possession of a noun
Their cat, their bookcase

They’re - conjunction of ‘they are’
Where are they going? They’re going to the movies
